      "role": "user",
      "content": "no its not just \"subconscious focus\" though. the jingle is literally the exact same pitch and tone as the one in the commercials i see during the day. and it's not like i've been looking at their stuff. i actually tried to avoid their ads entirely but it's happening in my sleep. it feels like they're bypassing my conscious mind. does that even make sense? like, can companies actually use some kind of frequency or signal to trigger stuff in your head while you sleep?",
